INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (3657,5,'2013-02-14 18:08:52','2013-02-14 18:08:52','Jeremy Wing is the founder of president of Payscape Advisers, which has grown from a local startup to a full-service merchant provider with $30 million in projected revenue and more than 125 employees in seven years. The company has been an Atlanta Business Chronicle Pacesetter for three straight years and has secured positions on Inc. Magazine’s annual Inc. 500 list of fastest-growing, privately-owned companies in the country.\r\n\r\nJeremy is a graduate of Dunwoody High School and the University of Alabama. During college, he began his entrepreneurial activities  by founding CampusCard, a discount card marketed toward college students. Jeremy’s post-education professional experience began with a successful six year career at MTV where, as the Director of Business Development for the Southeast, he was the youngest director in the company’s history.  It was during this time that Jeremy also founded the Peachtree Social Club, which still draws countless scores of Atlantans to social gatherings each year.\r\n\r\nJeremy is involved in a variety of community organizations, including the Buckhead Business Association, the Skyland Trail advisory board, Junior Achievement, The Shepherd Center and the Piedmont Park Conservancy. Jeremy has worked diligently with the Piedmont Park Conservancy to encourage young and upcoming professionals to focus on career development as well as community involvement.  Jeremy created the annual Dock Party to bring young professionals together for an evening of fun, philanthropy and awareness and, now in its fifth year, the event has raised more than $100,000 to provide maintenance, security and programming for Piedmont Park.\r\n\r\nJeremy is an avid outdoorsman who regularly tests his endurance by participating in triathlons and adventure races.  He has completed the Paris, San Diego, New York and Atlanta Marathons.  Furthermore, his adventurous nature has led him to summit some of the highest peaks in the continental United States, including Mount Rainer, Hood and Whitney.','Jeremy Wing','','publish','closed','closed','','jeremy-wing','','','2013-02-14 18:08:52','2013-02-14 18:08:52','',0,'http://flashpoint.ei2.org/?post_type=mentors&#038;p=3657',0,'mentors','',0);
