INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (4010,5,'2011-10-13 19:45:09','2011-10-13 19:45:09','<strong>PeHUB (8/31/11):</strong> A really large number of investor-financed startup incubators have cropped up over the past couple of years. That may be one reason a newer entrant — Atlanta-based Flashpoint — is taking pains to distinguish itself as an academia-led effort.\n\nHeadquartered on the campus of Georgia Tech, it’s about to begin working with its first group of local technology startups, who will get hooked up with mentors, training and a shot at seed funding. The effort’s academic roots came through in a conversation with Flashpoint’s director, Merrick Furst, who, about five minutes into the call, started sharing a list of must-read business books... <a href=\"http://www.pehub.com/login.php?p=/117124/3-must-read-biz-books-and-other-insights-from-flashpoint-incubators-co-director/?utm_source=feedburner&amp;utm_medium=feed&amp;utm_campaign=Feed%3A+pehub%2Fblog+%28PE+HUB+Blog%29\">read the rest</a> (requires subscription).\n\n&nbsp;','3 Must-Read Biz Books and Other Insights from Flashpoint Incubator’s Director','','inherit','closed','open','','326-revision','','','2011-10-13 19:45:09','2011-10-13 19:45:09','',326,'http://flashpoint.ei2.org/326-revision/',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (4011,5,'2011-10-13 19:30:18','2011-10-13 19:30:18','<strong>Southeast Tech Journal (8/31/11):</strong> ATLANTA – Georgia Tech Flashpoint, a new technology accelerator program run through the Georgia Institute of Technology, has selected its inaugural class of 18 teams invited to participate in the first cohort, which will run from September through December of 2011. It has also disclosed formation of the Flashpoint Investment Fund I.\n\nLed by Imlay President Sig Mosley, the $1 million risk capital fund will support startups in the first two Georgia Tech Flashpoint cohorts. The program, the first public-private partnership of its design in the country, brings together resources from the university, private funding and startup leaders to accelerate innovation and growth... <a href=\"http://www.techjournalsouth.com/2011/08/georgia-tech-flashpoint-accelerator-forms-1m-investment-fund/\">read the rest</a>.','Georgia Tech Flashpoint accelerator forms $1M investment fund','','inherit','closed','open','','323-revision','','','2011-10-13 19:30:18','2011-10-13 19:30:18','',323,'http://flashpoint.ei2.org/323-revision/',0,'revision','',0);
