INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (4023,5,'2013-02-19 15:24:46','2013-02-19 15:24:46','<strong>10,000 Startup Hours (1/10/12):</strong> Today I had a great time watching 15 startups in the <a href=\"http://flashpoint.gatech.edu/\">Flashpoint</a> cohort give six minute pitches at the Georgia Tech Research Institute. The teams have been working together since September 2011 and have made amazing progress.\r\n\r\nHere are notes from the 15 startups... <a href=\"http://davidcummings.org/2012/01/10/flashpoint-demo-day-startups-january-2012/\">Read more »</a>','Flashpoint Demo Day Startups January 2012','','inherit','closed','open','','751-revision-3','','','2013-02-19 15:24:46','2013-02-19 15:24:46','',751,'http://flashpoint.ei2.org/751-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (4024,5,'2013-02-19 15:27:03','2013-02-19 15:27:03','<strong>ATLANTA -- There is a very definite center to the Atlanta startup scene: it\'s the Starbucks located at 5th and Spring, just across I-85 from Georgia Tech\'s main campus.</strong>\r\n\r\n\"Most of the cool startup stuff is happening within half a mile of here,\" <a href=\"http://twitter.com/#%21/StephenFleming\">Stephen Fleming</a>, a long-time venture capitalist and technologist who runs GT\'s <a href=\"http://innovate.gatech.edu/\">Enterprise Innovation Institute</a>, told me.\r\n\r\nWe met at an event organized by a constellation of Atlanta startup community groups -- <a href=\"http://www.startupchicks.net/\">Startup Chicks</a>,<a href=\"http://twitter.com/#%21/atlsuds\">Atlanta Startup Drinks</a>, <a href=\"http://startupriot.com/\">Startup Riot</a>, the <a href=\"http://atdc.org/\">Advanced Technology Development Center</a> --  and sponsored by <a href=\"http://mailchimp.com/\">MailChimp</a>, an email marketing startup that I\'ve actually used myself.... <a href=\"http://www.theatlantic.com/technology/archive/2011/10/a-visual-guide-to-atlantas-startup-scene/247400/#\">Read more »</a>','A Visual Guide to Atlanta\'s Startup Scene','','inherit','closed','open','','399-revision-4','','','2013-02-19 15:27:03','2013-02-19 15:27:03','',399,'http://flashpoint.ei2.org/399-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (4025,5,'2013-02-19 15:29:04','2013-02-19 15:29:04','PC MAG\r\nTech Incubators: How Startups Are Born Today\r\n\r\nAtlanta has what it takes to incubate startups but not necessarily to maintain them. Georgia Institute of Technology professor Dan Breznitz authored a 2009 study that examined the issue. He attributed Atlanta’s failure to foster sustainable growth in the IT industry to “a lack of embeddedness of these companies in the Georgia economy, which in turn is caused by the societal fragmentation of the industry.” This September, Georgia Tech is going to try to turn that around with its own incubator,<a href=\"http://flashpoint.gatech.edu/\" target=\"_blank\">Flashpoint</a>... <a href=\"http://www.pcmag.com/slideshow/story/288707/tech-incubators-how-startups-are-born-today/3#fbid=yxkolldDCC9\">Read more »</a>....','Tech Incubators: How Startups Are Born Today','','inherit','closed','open','','274-revision-3','','','2013-02-19 15:29:04','2013-02-19 15:29:04','',274,'http://flashpoint.ei2.org/274-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (4026,5,'2013-02-19 15:30:09','2013-02-19 15:30:09','<strong>PeHUB (8/31/11):</strong> A really large number of investor-financed startup incubators have cropped up over the past couple of years. That may be one reason a newer entrant — Atlanta-based Flashpoint — is taking pains to distinguish itself as an academia-led effort.\r\n\r\nHeadquartered on the campus of Georgia Tech, it’s about to begin working with its first group of local technology startups, who will get hooked up with mentors, training and a shot at seed funding. The effort’s academic roots came through in a conversation with Flashpoint’s director, Merrick Furst, who, about five minutes into the call, started sharing a list of must-read business books... <a href=\"http://www.pehub.com/login.php?p=/117124/3-must-read-biz-books-and-other-insights-from-flashpoint-incubators-co-director/?utm_source=feedburner&amp;utm_medium=feed&amp;utm_campaign=Feed%3A+pehub%2Fblog+%28PE+HUB+Blog%29\">Read more »</a> (requires subscription).','3 Must-Read Biz Books and Other Insights from Flashpoint Incubator’s Director','','inherit','closed','open','','326-revision-2','','','2013-02-19 15:30:09','2013-02-19 15:30:09','',326,'http://flashpoint.ei2.org/326-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (4027,5,'2013-02-19 15:30:45','2013-02-19 15:30:45','<strong>Southeast Tech Journal (8/31/11):</strong> ATLANTA – Georgia Tech Flashpoint, a new technology accelerator program run through the Georgia Institute of Technology, has selected its inaugural class of 18 teams invited to participate in the first cohort, which will run from September through December of 2011. It has also disclosed formation of the Flashpoint Investment Fund I.\r\n\r\nLed by Imlay President Sig Mosley, the $1 million risk capital fund will support startups in the first two Georgia Tech Flashpoint cohorts. The program, the first public-private partnership of its design in the country, brings together resources from the university, private funding and startup leaders to accelerate innovation and growth... <a href=\"http://www.techjournalsouth.com/2011/08/georgia-tech-flashpoint-accelerator-forms-1m-investment-fund/\">Read more »</a>.','Georgia Tech Flashpoint accelerator forms $1M investment fund','','inherit','closed','open','','323-revision-2','','','2013-02-19 15:30:45','2013-02-19 15:30:45','',323,'http://flashpoint.ei2.org/323-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (4028,5,'2013-02-19 15:31:14','2013-02-19 15:31:14','<strong>Atlanta Business Chronicle (8/31/11):</strong> Flashpoint, backed by a nearly $1 million fund, will launch its inaugural class of tech startups on Sept. 7.\r\n\r\nThe Georgia Tech “accelerator,” plans for which were reported first on this blog in May, will invest up to $25,000 in each of the startups and help them develop scalable businesses.\r\n\r\nThe program hopes to lure promising technology, medical device and biotech startups to metro Atlanta.\r\n\r\nThe new venture also hopes to address one of the biggest issues facing Atlanta\'s startup community — a lack of early stage,  local capital... <a href=\"http://www.bizjournals.com/atlanta/blog/atlantech/2011/08/accelerator-flashpoint-launches-first.html?page=all\">Read more »</a>.','Accelerator Flashpoint launches, raises $1 million fund','','inherit','closed','open','','321-revision-3','','','2013-02-19 15:31:14','2013-02-19 15:31:14','',321,'http://flashpoint.ei2.org/321-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0);
