INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (4039,5,'2013-02-19 15:36:36','2013-02-19 15:36:36','<strong>PeHUB (8/31/11):</strong> A really large number of investor-financed startup incubators have cropped up over the past couple of years. That may be one reason a newer entrant — Atlanta-based Flashpoint — is taking pains to distinguish itself as an academia-led effort.\r\n\r\nHeadquartered on the campus of Georgia Tech, it’s about to begin working with its first group of local technology startups, who will get hooked up with mentors, training and a shot at seed funding. The effort’s academic roots came through in a conversation with Flashpoint’s director, Merrick Furst, who, about five minutes into the call, started sharing a list of must-read business books... <a href=\"http://www.pehub.com/login.php?p=/117124/3-must-read-biz-books-and-other-insights-from-flashpoint-incubators-co-director/?utm_source=feedburner&amp;utm_medium=feed&amp;utm_campaign=Feed%3A+pehub%2Fblog+%28PE+HUB+Blog%29\">Read more »</a> (requires subscription).','3 Must-Read Biz Books and Other Insights from Flashpoint Incubator’s Director','','inherit','closed','open','','326-revision-3','','','2013-02-19 15:36:36','2013-02-19 15:36:36','',326,'http://flashpoint.ei2.org/326-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (4040,5,'2013-02-19 15:36:41','2013-02-19 15:36:41','<strong>Southeast Tech Journal (8/31/11):</strong> ATLANTA – Georgia Tech Flashpoint, a new technology accelerator program run through the Georgia Institute of Technology, has selected its inaugural class of 18 teams invited to participate in the first cohort, which will run from September through December of 2011. It has also disclosed formation of the Flashpoint Investment Fund I.\r\n\r\nLed by Imlay President Sig Mosley, the $1 million risk capital fund will support startups in the first two Georgia Tech Flashpoint cohorts. The program, the first public-private partnership of its design in the country, brings together resources from the university, private funding and startup leaders to accelerate innovation and growth... <a href=\"http://www.techjournalsouth.com/2011/08/georgia-tech-flashpoint-accelerator-forms-1m-investment-fund/\">Read more »</a>.','Georgia Tech Flashpoint accelerator forms $1M investment fund','','inherit','closed','open','','323-revision-3','','','2013-02-19 15:36:41','2013-02-19 15:36:41','',323,'http://flashpoint.ei2.org/323-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (4041,5,'2013-02-19 15:36:47','2013-02-19 15:36:47','<strong>Atlanta Business Chronicle (8/31/11):</strong> Flashpoint, backed by a nearly $1 million fund, will launch its inaugural class of tech startups on Sept. 7.\r\n\r\nThe Georgia Tech “accelerator,” plans for which were reported first on this blog in May, will invest up to $25,000 in each of the startups and help them develop scalable businesses.\r\n\r\nThe program hopes to lure promising technology, medical device and biotech startups to metro Atlanta.\r\n\r\nThe new venture also hopes to address one of the biggest issues facing Atlanta\'s startup community — a lack of early stage,  local capital... <a href=\"http://www.bizjournals.com/atlanta/blog/atlantech/2011/08/accelerator-flashpoint-launches-first.html?page=all\">Read more »</a>.','Accelerator Flashpoint launches, raises $1 million fund','','inherit','closed','open','','321-revision-4','','','2013-02-19 15:36:47','2013-02-19 15:36:47','',321,'http://flashpoint.ei2.org/321-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (4042,5,'2013-02-19 15:36:58','2013-02-19 15:36:58','<strong>Global Atlanta (8/30/11):</strong> The executive who runs Israel\'s top business incubator praised the Georgia Institute of Technology\'s holistic approach to getting tech companies off the ground.\r\n\r\n\"I\'ve never seen anything like it,\" said Todd Dollinger, chairman and CEO of The Trendlines Group, after visiting Tech\'sAdvance Technology Development Center, or ATDC... He was especially impressed by Georgia Tech\'s upcoming Flashpoint program, which follows an industry trend based on the model pioneered by Silicon Valley\'s Y Combinator incubator... <a href=\"http://www.globalatlanta.com/article/25030/\">Read more »</a>.','CEO Behind Israel\'s Top Incubator Praises Georgia Tech','','inherit','closed','open','','328-revision-4','','','2013-02-19 15:36:58','2013-02-19 15:36:58','',328,'http://flashpoint.ei2.org/328-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0);
