INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (4117,5,'2013-02-20 15:16:59','2013-02-20 15:16:59','Experienced Technology Executive and CEO; has built several successful Internet businesses. Currently: CEO of FlashIssue, a new venture that brings a different twist to content marketing through email and social media.\r\n\r\nPreviously: CEO of Openstudy, a start-up company that provides a collaborative study social network for high school and college students. Co-Founder of Netzip.com, a company that established the de facto standard for downloading software &amp;amp; music files on the Internet. The company was acquired by RealNetworks. Vice President of MusicNet (subsidiary of RealNetworks), a company that pioneered the early music subscription models adopted by Yahoo, AOL and MTV.\r\n\r\nCo-Founder of Vocalocity, a market leading telecom startup providing cloud based VOIP phone services to small companies. Started in 1989 at Coca-Cola &amp;amp; Schweppes in the UK as a marketing manager, before moving into technology.  From 2001-2, worked as Interim Executive Director of an ailing non-profit called Soccer In The Streets; introduced a new vision to get at-risk kids off the streets and away from drugs and crime in 19 cities across the U.S.\r\n\r\nAlso, an avid mountain biker, a retired Improv actor and obsessive builder of tree houses. A UK native, who arrived in the US in 1993 with a backpack, $267 and a passion to be curious.','Phil Hill','','publish','closed','closed','','phil-hill','','','2013-02-20 15:16:59','2013-02-20 15:16:59','',0,'http://flashpoint.ei2.org/?post_type=mentors&#038;p=4117',0,'mentors','',0);
